Introduction

Jin Hyeon Jun, also known by his stage name JINN, is a South Korean YouTuber and singer renowned for his exceptional ability to mimic over 100 different voices, including prominent artists like K.Will, Jang Beom June, Jannabi, Lee Soo Young, and Kim Jin Ho.

YouTube Career: JINN has built a substantial following on YouTube, where he showcases his vocal versatility through various song covers and live performances. He engages with his audience through live broadcasts titled "Jin Hyun Jun's Daily Sseun," held every Sunday, Monday, and Tuesday from 10 PM to 12 AM KST, featuring singing sessions and interactive discussions.

On March 9, 2024, JINN made his official singing debut with the single album 'Farewell Diary', marking his transition from a YouTuber to a professional singer.
